        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8280",
        "content": "\"'The half dozen cigars which most smokers use a day, contain six or seven grains-enough, if concentrated and absorbed, to kill three men, and a pound of tobacco, according to its quality, contains from one quarter to one and a quarter ounces.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-high_s-normal_e-low",
